gFU(){return"I'm strong"},
gFV(){return"I'm kind"},
gFJ(){return"Something About Me"},
gFK(){return"Hi!\nI'm Stefano, an Italian software developer (class '91).\n\nI lived for most of my life in a town in Southern Italy. I got the bachelor's degree there and then moved to Northern Italy to get the master's degree in computer science.\nI moved in Sunnyvale, California, for 6 months to work in a startup and then moved back to my town to work for a local company.\nCurrently I'm working from home for a Californian startup.\n\nI was always interested with computers, but started programming only in university, and found myself really enjoy it. Probably because I like to learn new things, experiment and understand how they work.\nThat's why I do my best to keep up with the latest technologies: I like doing it!\nIn fact I always look for new challenges, both professionally and personally.\n\nOf course, computers and programming are not my only interest. Here is a selection of some of my previous (mostly temporary) interests."},
gGj(){return"Past Interests"},
gG6(){return"Play Guitar"},
gG5(){return"I tried to learn playing the guitar.\nAnd I did it!\n\nI could even play at least two songs!"},
